fields.name: pi__Pardot_Last_Scored_At__c
fields.description:
Used for Account Engagement Scoring Categories. Indicates the last time a Scoring Category score was updated for this contact.

            Scoring Categories are used for multi-product engagement scoring in Account Engagement and are available to customers using Account Engagement Pro Edition and Account Engagement Ultimate Edition. Please visit this page for more information on this feature and how to set up Salesforce to view these scores: http://help.pardot.com/customer/portal/articles/2396977-scoring-categories-overview

fields.name: pi__campaign__c
fields.description: The Account Engagement Campaign represents the first marketing touch with a prospect. It may be a campaign associated with your web site, landing page, paid search initiative, or any other marketing effort. Prospects may only be associated with one Account Engagement campaign. This value can later be changed manually or via an Automation Rule.

fields.name: pi__conversion_date__c
fields.description: The date and time of the form, form handler, or landing page submission when an Account Engagement tracked anonymous visitor first became a known prospect.

fields.name: pi__conversion_object_name__c
fields.description: This is the name of the object (form, form handler, landing page, or video form) that converted an anonymous visitor into a named prospect.

fields.name: pi__conversion_object_type__c
fields.description: The type of object which converted an anonymous visitor into a named prospect (form, form handler, landing page, or video form).

fields.name: pi__created_date__c
fields.description: The Account Engagement created date represents the date and time at which the Prospect record was created in Account Engagement. This will often differ from your Salesforce.com created date.

fields.name: pi__first_search_term__c
fields.description: If a Prospects first touch was the result of a search, this field contains the search term.

fields.name: pi__first_search_type__c
fields.description: If a Prospects first touch was the result of a search, this field contains the type of search conducted.

fields.name: pi__first_touch_url__c
fields.description: The value of the referrer for the first tracked request made by a Prospect.

fields.name: pi__grade__c
fields.description: The Account Engagement grade is based on how well a prospect fits your organization's ideal customer profile. Explicit factors such as company size, industry, job title and more help determine this value. A combination of grade (explicit) and score (implicit) can be used to very effectively optimize the sales team's time. Grade, like score, is calculated within the Account Engagement system and cannot be edited in Salesforce.com.

fields.name: pi__pardot_hard_bounced__c
fields.description: Boolean that determines whether contact hard bounced.

fields.name: pi__score__c
fields.description: The Account Engagement score is based on implicit buying signals a lead demonstrates through his or her activities and responses to your marketing efforts. The higher the score, the more active the lead has been. A combination of score (implicit buying signals) and grade (explicit factors) helps you prioritize your prospects. Score, like grade, is calculated within the Account Engagement system and cannot be edited in Salesforce.com.

fields.name: pi__url__c
fields.description: This link takes you directly into the relevant prospect's profile within Account Engagement. From there you can view his or her complete activity history. This URL is generated within the Account Engagement system and cannot be edited in Salesforce.com.

fields.name: pi__campaign__c
fields.description: The Account Engagement Campaign represents the first marketing touch with a prospect. It may be a campaign associated with your web site, landing page, paid search initiative, or any other marketing effort. Prospects may only be associated with one Account Engagement campaign. This value can later be changed manually or via an Automation Rule.

fields.name: pi__conversion_date__c
fields.description: The date and time of the form, form handler, or landing page submission when an Account Engagement tracked anonymous visitor first became a known prospect.

fields.name: pi__conversion_object_name__c
fields.description: This is the name of the object (form, form handler, landing page, or video form) that converted an anonymous visitor into a named prospect.

fields.name: pi__conversion_object_type__c
fields.description: The type of object which converted an anonymous visitor into a named prospect (form, form handler, landing page, or video form).

fields.name: pi__created_date__c
fields.description: The Account Engagement created date represents the date and time at which the Prospect record was created in Account Engagement. This will often differ from your Salesforce.com created date.

fields.name: pi__first_search_term__c
fields.description: If a Prospects first touch was the result of a search, the field holds the term that was searched on.

fields.name: pi__first_search_type__c
fields.description: If a Prospects first touch was the result of a search, this field contains the type of search conducted.

fields.name: pi__first_touch_url__c
fields.description: The value of the referrer for the first tracked request made by a Prospect.

fields.name: pi__grade__c
fields.description: The Account Engagement grade is based on how well a prospect fits your organization's ideal customer profile. Explicit factors such as company size, industry, job title and more help determine this value. A combination of grade (explicit) and score (implicit) can be used to very effectively optimize the sales team's time. Grade, like score, is calculated within the Account Engagement system and cannot be edited in Salesforce.com.

fields.name: pi__pardot_hard_bounced__c
fields.description: Boolean that determines whether lead hard bounced.

fields.name: pi__score__c
fields.description: The Account Engagement score is based on implicit buying signals a lead demonstrates through his or her activities and responses to your marketing efforts. The higher the score, the more active the lead has been. A combination of score (implicit buying signals) and grade (explicit factors) helps you prioritize your prospects. Score, like grade, is calculated within the Account Engagement system and cannot be edited in Salesforce.com.

fields.name: pi__url__c
fields.description: This link takes you directly into the relevant prospect's profile within Account Engagement. From there you can view his or her complete activity history. This URL is generated within the Account Engagement system and cannot be edited in Salesforce.com.

fields.name: SBQQ__Selected__c
fields.description: Indicates this option should be selected by default.

fields.name: SBQQ__SubscriptionScope__c
fields.description: Specifies percent of total calculation scope for percent of total priced products added as product options.

fields.name: SBQQ__System__c
fields.description: Marks this option as managed by the system which means users can not manually select or deselect.

fields.name: SBQQ__Type__c
fields.description: Type of this option.

fields.name: SBQQ__UnitPrice__c
fields.description: Unit price for this option. This will override the value from price book.

fields.name: SBQQ__UpliftedByPackage__c
fields.description: Check to automatically apply uplift from parent package to this component. Only applies to components that are multi-segmented products.

name: Product Rule
description: Rule that governs valid product configurations.

fields.name: External_ID__c
fields.description: Used by Data Packs to identify and update records.

fields.name: SBQQ__Active__c
fields.description: Flag that indicates whether this rule is active or inactive.

fields.name: SBQQ__AdvancedCondition__c
fields.description: Can only be entered if the Conditions Met is Custom. Enter a combination of the Error Condition Index #s, AND, OR, and parenthesis (e.g. (123 AND 124) AND 125).

fields.name: SBQQ__ConditionsMet__c
fields.description: Choose the behavior for your conditions: All is AND, Any is OR, Custom is a combination of AND/OR.

fields.name: SBQQ__ErrorMessage__c
fields.description: Enter a message to displayed when rule is activated.  An error message will be displayed when a Validations is fired.  A warning message will be displayed when an Alert is fired. Does not apply to Filter rules.

fields.name: SBQQ__EvaluationEvent__c
fields.description: Event that causes this rule to be evaluated.

fields.name: SBQQ__EvaluationOrder__c
fields.description: Order in which this price rule is evaluated.

fields.name: SBQQ__LookupMessageField__c
fields.description: Field on Lookup Object corresponding to Product Rule Message. Field must be text.

fields.name: SBQQ__LookupObject__c
fields.description: API Name of the Custom Object that stores the lookup data.

fields.name: SBQQ__LookupProductField__c
fields.description: Field on Lookup Object corresponding to Product Action Product Lookup. Field must be a lookup to the Product object.

fields.name: SBQQ__LookupRequiredField__c
fields.description: Field on Lookup Object corresponding to Product Action Required checkbox. Field must be checkbox.

fields.name: SBQQ__LookupTypeField__c
fields.description: Field on Lookup Object corresponding to Product Action Type picklist. Field must be a Picklist or Text.

fields.name: SBQQ__Scope__c
fields.description: Scopes the rule to the entire quote or specific product.

fields.name: SBQQ__Type__c
fields.description: Type of rule. Validation displays error messages. Selection causes products to be added or suggested. Alert displays a warning, but requires no rectification. Filter refines option lookup results for Dynamic Bundles.

name: Quote Document
description: Particular version of a generated PDF document for the quote it's attached to. Ability to edit or delete this object should be taken away from all users (except administrators, of course) in order to preserve audit trail of all revisions.

fields.name: External_ID__c
fields.description: Used by Data Packs to identify and update records.

fields.name: SBQQ__AttachmentId__c
fields.description: ID of attachment record generated for this document.

fields.name: SBQQ__CustomerAmount__c
fields.description: Customer amount on the quote at the time this document was generated.

fields.name: SBQQ__DocumentId__c
fields.description: ID of the Document record which contains its generated PDF.

fields.name: SBQQ__ElectronicSignature__c
fields.description: Indicates this document was generated for electronic signature.

fields.name: SBQQ__Key__c
fields.description: Key used to ensure unique combination of quote ID and version number.

fields.name: SBQQ__ListAmount__c
fields.description: List amount of the quote at the time this document was generated.

fields.name: SBQQ__NetAmount__c
fields.description: Net amount on the quote at the time this document was generated.

fields.name: SBQQ__Opportunity__c
fields.description: Lookup to the Opportunity that parents the Quote for this document. References the opportunity on the quote for this document, allowing the Opportunity Quote Documents Related List to reside on the Opportunity as well as the Quote.

fields.name: SBQQ__OutputFormat__c
fields.description: Output format of this document.

fields.name: SBQQ__PaperSize__c
fields.description: Paper size of this document.

fields.name: SBQQ__PrimaryContactId__c
fields.description: ID of primary contact in the quote. Used in Email button to default the To field.

fields.name: SBQQ__QuoteTemplate__c
fields.description: Quote Template that generated this document.

fields.name: SBQQ__Quote__c
fields.description: Quote to which this Quote Document belongs.

fields.name: SBQQ__SignatureStatus__c
fields.description: Status of electronic signature.

fields.name: SBQQ__Template__c
fields.description: Name of the template used to generate this document.

fields.name: SBQQ__Version__c
fields.description: Sequentially incremented version number.

fields.name: SBQQ__ViewRecordId__c
fields.description: Allows user to view the Quote Document Record Id.

fields.name: External_ID__c
fields.description: Used by Data Packs to identify and update records.

fields.name: SBQQ__LowerBound__c
fields.description: The lowest quantity of usage for this consumption rate.

fields.name: SBQQ__Price__c
fields.description: The price for usage that falls within this consumption rate's bounds.

fields.name: SBQQ__ProcessingOrder__c
fields.description: The order for processing the usage rate across multiple rates. Consumption Rates are evaluated beginning with the lowest processing order.

fields.name: SBQQ__QuoteLineConsumptionSchedule__c
fields.description: This rate is a part of of this schedule.

fields.name: SBQQ__UpperBound__c
fields.description: The highest quantity of usage for this consumption rate.

fields.name: External_ID__c
fields.description: Used by Data Packs to identify and update records.

fields.name: SBQQ__BillingTermUnit__c
fields.description: The unit used with the billing term to determine the billing frequency.

fields.name: SBQQ__BillingTerm__c
fields.description: The number used with the billing term unit to determine the billing frequency.

fields.name: SBQQ__MatchingAttribute__c
fields.description: Usage is matched with a consumption schedule if the records share the same Matching Attribute value.

fields.name: SBQQ__RatingMethod__c
fields.description: Choose a specific use case to rate usage against this schedule. This is a controlling picklist for the Type field.

fields.name: SBQQ__Type__c
fields.description: Range: The schedule prices only using the tier that applies to the usage quantity. Slab: Usage within a given bound receives pricing equal to its tier's value

fields.name: SBQQ__UnitOfMeasure__c
fields.description: Usage quantities and rates apply to this unit of measurement.

name: Quote Line Group
description: Group of line items on a quote.

fields.name: External_ID__c
fields.description: Used by Data Packs to identify and update records.

fields.name: SBQQ__Account__c
fields.description: Account to which this Quote Line Group references.

fields.name: SBQQ__AdditionalDiscountRate__c
fields.description: Default additional discount rate applied to line items in this group.

fields.name: SBQQ__BillingFrequency__c
fields.description: Defines the billing frequency.

fields.name: SBQQ__CustomerTotal__c
fields.description: Total for this group's line items before any partner discounts are applied.

fields.name: SBQQ__Description__c
fields.description: Description for this group.

fields.name: SBQQ__EndDate__c
fields.description: End date for subscriptions in this group.

fields.name: SBQQ__Favorite__c
fields.description: Favorite to which this Quote Line Group belongs.

fields.name: SBQQ__ListTotal__c
fields.description: Total for this group's line items before any discounts are applied.

fields.name: SBQQ__MarkupRate__c
fields.description: Default markup rate applied to line items in this group.

fields.name: SBQQ__NetTotal__c
fields.description: Total for this group's line items after all discounts are applied.

fields.name: SBQQ__Number__c
fields.description: Sort order of this group within its quote.

fields.name: SBQQ__Optional__c
fields.description: Marks the entire group as optional.

fields.name: SBQQ__QuoteProcess__c
fields.description: Quote process used with this group.

fields.name: SBQQ__Quote__c
fields.description: Quote to which this group belongs.

fields.name: SBQQ__SeparateContract__c
fields.description: Flag that forces a separate contract for this group.

fields.name: SBQQ__SolutionGroup__c
fields.description: Solution group from which this quote group was generated (if any).

fields.name: SBQQ__Source__c
fields.description: Source of cloned quote line group.

fields.name: SBQQ__StartDate__c
fields.description: Start date for subscriptions in this group.

fields.name: SBQQ__SubscriptionTerm__c
fields.description: Subscription term used to prorate eligible products in this group.

fields.name: SBQQ__TargetCustomerAmount__c
fields.description: Customer amount to be targeted in calculating additional discounts.

name: Quote Line Pricing Guidance
description: The accepted pricing guidance on a quote line

fields.name: External_ID__c
fields.description: Used by Data Packs to identify and update records.

fields.name: SBQQ__Explanation__c
fields.description: An explanation of this pricing guidance and recommendations for discounts to provide. Sales reps can view this explanation with the pricing guidance in the quote line editor.

fields.name: SBQQ__Floor__c
fields.description: High discount for exception pricing based on past sales. If a sales rep wants to use this price, they must discount the quote line manually. This discount may require approvals based on your org's approval settings.

fields.name: SBQQ__GuidanceUsed__c
fields.description: A sales rep has accepted the target discount from this pricing guidance in the quote line editor.

fields.name: SBQQ__IsViewed__c
fields.description: A sales rep has viewed this pricing guidance in the quote line editor.

fields.name: SBQQ__Norm__c
fields.description: Middle-range discount based on past sales. If a sales rep wants to use this price, they must discount the quote line manually. This discount may require approvals based on your org's approval settings.

fields.name: SBQQ__QuoteLine__c
fields.description: The quote line related to this pricing guidance.

fields.name: SBQQ__Quote__c
fields.description: The quote containing the quote line related to this pricing guidance.

fields.name: SBQQ__Target__c
fields.description: Ideal low-range discount based on past sales. If sales reps accept this pricing guidance, Salesforce CPQ applies a discount to reach this price.

name: Quote Line
description: Individual line item on a quote.

fields.name: Approval__c
fields.description: Icon preview of the necessary approval based on discretionary discount.

fields.name: External_ID__c
fields.description: Used by Data Packs to identify and update records.

fields.name: SBQQ__AdditionalDiscountAmount__c
fields.description: Additional customer discount extended on this line item in terms of absolute amount.

fields.name: SBQQ__AdditionalDiscount__c
fields.description: Total additional discount extends on this line item. Additional discount is defined as discount extended on top of volume discount or negotiated prices.

fields.name: SBQQ__AdditionalQuantity__c
fields.description: Additional quantity for this product which contributes to volume discount calculations.

fields.name: SBQQ__AllowAssetRefund__c
fields.description: Indicates whether the underlying asset may have its quantity refunded. Only relevant for Amendments.

fields.name: SBQQ__BatchQuantity__c
fields.description: For products sold in batches quantity in each batch. Defaulted from the product record.

fields.name: SBQQ__BillingFrequency__c
fields.description: Defines the billing frequency.

fields.name: SBQQ__BillingType__c
fields.description: The billing type that defines when the billing occurs. Billing in advance lets you bill your customers for products or services before you provide them; Billing in arrears lets you bill your customers after the products or services are provided.

fields.name: SBQQ__BlockPrice__c
fields.description: Assign a fixed price to a product based on quantity and quantity range. This overrides the automatic calculation of quantity * unit price.

fields.name: SBQQ__Bundle__c
fields.description: Indicates whether this line item represents a package; meaning, it includes other line items in this quote.

fields.name: SBQQ__BundledQuantity__c
fields.description: For items with calculated quantities this field hold the original (user entered) quantity.

fields.name: SBQQ__Bundled__c
fields.description: Indicates the product on this line item is bundled (included) by another product in this quote. Bundled lines items are zero price and do not allow price or quantity to be edited.

fields.name: SBQQ__CarryoverLine__c
fields.description: Denotes this line as an auto-mapped option on an Upgraded Bundle.

fields.name: SBQQ__ChargeType__c
fields.description: The type of the product charge.  This is a system field that is derived from the associated product.

fields.name: SBQQ__ComponentCost__c
fields.description: Total cost of components in this package.

fields.name: SBQQ__ComponentDiscountedByPackage__c
fields.description: Fixes additional discount for this component to the parent package discount.

fields.name: SBQQ__ComponentListTotal__c
fields.description: List total of components in this configuration. This field is only populated if this line item references configurable product.

fields.name: SBQQ__ComponentSubscriptionScope__c
fields.description: Subscription scope set at the component level. This field overrides the subscriptions cope copied from the product.

fields.name: SBQQ__ComponentTotal__c
fields.description: Sum total of components in this configuration. This field is only populated if this line item references configurable product.

fields.name: SBQQ__ComponentUpliftedByPackage__c
fields.description: Fixes uplift for this component to the parent package uplift. Uplift only applies to multi-segmented products.

fields.name: SBQQ__ComponentVisibility__c
fields.description: Visibility of this component line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__CompoundDiscountRate__c
fields.description: Discount rate compounded by quantity (historic).

fields.name: SBQQ__ConfigurationRequired__c
fields.description: Flag that marks this quote line as requiring configuration. Can be used by custom code to request this product be re-configured.

fields.name: SBQQ__ContractedPrice__c
fields.description: Contracted price if the product has negotiated pricing for opportunity's account. Contracted Prices are available on the Account and can be applied to any product in any price book.

fields.name: SBQQ__CostEditable__c
fields.description: Specifies whether cost can be edited on this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__Cost__c
fields.description: Cost record for this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__CustomerPrice__c
fields.description: Customer unit price for the product quoted by this line item. This is the Net Unit Price excluding any partner discounts.

fields.name: SBQQ__CustomerTotal__c
fields.description: Customer total price for this quote line item. This is the Net Total excluding any partner discounts.

fields.name: SBQQ__DefaultSubscriptionTerm__c
fields.description: Term length of the subscription, which only applies if the product is a subscription. It is copied from the Subscription Term of the related product when the line item is first generated.

fields.name: SBQQ__Description__c
fields.description: Description for this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__Dimension__c
fields.description: Dimensions within an MDQ Product that all each segment to be priced independently. Each Product may contain several Price Dimensions. Yearly Price Dimensions are treated as Subscriptions.

fields.name: SBQQ__DiscountScheduleType__c
fields.description: Discount schedule type. Must be a stored value because it's used in formula fields that are rolled up.

fields.name: SBQQ__DiscountSchedule__c
fields.description: Specify discounts in terms of % or Amt to be discounted off the product's price using quantity purchased or term. Set quantity/term ranges in tiers of different discount %. Discount is applied to List Price & resulting total is stored in the Regular Price

fields.name: SBQQ__DiscountTier__c
fields.description: Discount tier used by this line item. This field is only populated if a product is volume discounted and discount schedule is of type "Range".

fields.name: SBQQ__Discount__c
fields.description: Additional customer discount extended for this line item expressed in terms of percentage.

fields.name: SBQQ__DistributorDiscount__c
fields.description: This is a discount that is applied to partner price and reflected in the net price.

fields.name: SBQQ__DynamicOptionId__c
fields.description: Contains feature id and product id to identify the feature and optional SKU associated with this line.

fields.name: SBQQ__EarliestValidAmendmentStartDate__c
fields.description: The earliest safe date for an amendment quote line to start before it becomes back-dated and therefore forbidden.

fields.name: SBQQ__EffectiveEndDate__c
fields.description: Effective end date for this subscription.

fields.name: SBQQ__EffectiveQuantity__c
fields.description: Effective quantity used in computing totals. Same as quantity unless the product is block priced, covered by "Slab" discount schedule, or an existing subscription.

fields.name: SBQQ__EffectiveStartDate__c
fields.description: Effective start date for this subscription.

fields.name: SBQQ__EffectiveSubscriptionTerm__c
fields.description: Effective term for this subscription.

fields.name: SBQQ__EndDate__c
fields.description: Date the service represented by this line item will end (only applies if product is a subscription).

fields.name: SBQQ__Existing__c
fields.description: Indicates the customer already owns this product. This is typically used for products with options during add-on quoting. The product is on the quote solely to drive the Configurator.

fields.name: SBQQ__Favorite__c
fields.description: Favorite to which this Quote Line belongs.

fields.name: SBQQ__GenerateContractedPrice__c
fields.description: Will generate a contracted price based on the adjusted quote line if flagged.

fields.name: SBQQ__GrossProfit__c
fields.description: Gross profit amount on this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__Group__c
fields.description: Group to which this line belongs, if any.

fields.name: SBQQ__Guidance__c
fields.description: Ideal low-range discount based on past sales. If sales reps accept this pricing guidance, Salesforce CPQ applies a discount to reach this price.

fields.name: SBQQ__HasConsumptionSchedule__c
fields.description: Indicates if the Quote Line has at least one consumption schedule

fields.name: SBQQ__Hidden__c
fields.description: Denotes whether this line item is hidden in generated PDF documents.

fields.name: SBQQ__Incomplete__c
fields.description: Flag set internally by application logic when a line is saved to an incomplete database. This may happen when price rules are evaluated. Test this field in validation rules to avoid them firing prematurely. Do NOT add to page layout or otherwise update.

fields.name: SBQQ__ListPrice__c
fields.description: List unit price for the product quoted by this line item. List Price originates from the price book.

fields.name: SBQQ__ListTotal__c
fields.description: List total price for this quote line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__MarkupAmount__c
fields.description: Markup amount for this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__MarkupRate__c
fields.description: Markup on this line item expressed as a percentage.

fields.name: SBQQ__Markup__c
fields.description: Markup amount on this item. This value is automatically calculated by applying markup rate or absolute amount to the product cost.

fields.name: SBQQ__MaximumPrice__c
fields.description: Maximum list unit price for this product. Used to enforce list price ceiling for products with dynamically calculated list prices.

fields.name: SBQQ__MinimumPrice__c
fields.description: Minimum list unit price for this product. Used to enforce list price floor for products with dynamically calculated list prices.

fields.name: SBQQ__NetPrice__c
fields.description: Net unit price for the product quoted by this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__NetTotal__c
fields.description: Net total price for this quote line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__NonDiscountable__c
fields.description: Marks this line item as non-discountable.

fields.name: SBQQ__NonPartnerDiscountable__c
fields.description: Marks this line item non discountable for partners.

fields.name: SBQQ__Number__c
fields.description: Number indicating this line's position within its group or quote.

fields.name: SBQQ__OptionDiscountAmount__c
fields.description: Discount extended on this product because it's part of a package.

fields.name: SBQQ__OptionDiscount__c
fields.description: If this line is for an optional SKU, this field captures any discount given to the package and extended to the option.

fields.name: SBQQ__OptionLevel__c
fields.description: Indicates nest level of this option (only applies to lines that are generated from options).

fields.name: SBQQ__OptionType__c
fields.description: Indicates the Option Type, which is copied from related Product Option. Determines how quantity is calculated.

fields.name: SBQQ__Optional__c
fields.description: Marks this line as optional. Optional line items don't contribute to quote totals and are not transferred to the Opportunity.

fields.name: SBQQ__OriginalPrice__c
fields.description: The original unit price for the product quoted by this line item.  Original Price originates from the price book.  Also known as MSRP.

fields.name: SBQQ__OriginalQuoteLineId__c
fields.description: The id of the original quote line which this line was derived from.

fields.name: SBQQ__OriginalUnitCost__c
fields.description: Cost for one unit of product quoted on this line item if Cost Schedules were not applied.

fields.name: SBQQ__PackageCost__c
fields.description: Total cost for this package including the cost of its components.

fields.name: SBQQ__PackageListTotal__c
fields.description: Total list price of this package including its components.

fields.name: SBQQ__PackageProductCode__c
fields.description: Product code for the package generated by appending codes of selected components according to specified pattern.

fields.name: SBQQ__PackageProductDescription__c
fields.description: Product Description for the package generated by appending descriptions of selected components according to specified pattern.

fields.name: SBQQ__PackageTotal__c
fields.description: Total price of this package including its components.

fields.name: SBQQ__PartnerDiscount__c
fields.description: If your organization sells through a channel/VARl, you can give a “partner discount” on quote or the individual product line item on the quote. By default, partner discounts are applied after all automatic and discretionary discounts. The partner discount is taken into account in the Partner Price.

fields.name: SBQQ__PartnerPrice__c
fields.description: Partner unit price. Price after partner discount but before distributor discount.

fields.name: SBQQ__PartnerTotal__c
fields.description: Total of the Partner Discount. By default, partner discounts are applied after all automatic and discretionary discounts. The partner discount is taken into account in the Partner Price.

fields.name: SBQQ__PreviousSegmentPrice__c
fields.description: When set, this value takes the place of the previous segment's regular price when calculating Uplift for this segment.

fields.name: SBQQ__PreviousSegmentUplift__c
fields.description: When set, this value takes the place of the previous segment's uplift amount when calculating Uplift for this segment.

fields.name: SBQQ__PriceEditable__c
fields.description: Flag that indicates if price is editable for this line item

fields.name: SBQQ__PricingMethodEditable__c
fields.description: Specifies whether pricing method can be edited on this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__PricingMethod__c
fields.description: Determines how the price for this line item is set. "List" = calculated by subtracting discount from list price. "Cost"  = calculated by adding markup to cost.

fields.name: SBQQ__PriorQuantity__c
fields.description: Combined quantity of this product from prior purchases.

fields.name: SBQQ__ProductCode__c
fields.description: Code for the product referenced by this line.

fields.name: SBQQ__ProductFamily__c
fields.description: How you would categorize/group/organize this within Salesforce (whether it's a new or existing Product Family). Additionally, this field can be used during product selection to filter to the correct product or product SKU.

fields.name: SBQQ__ProductName__c
fields.description: Name for the product referenced by this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__ProductOption__c
fields.description: Product option that generated this line (if any).

fields.name: SBQQ__ProductSubscriptionType__c
fields.description: Set the quote line's product subscription type.

fields.name: SBQQ__Product__c
fields.description: Product quoted by this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__ProrateMultiplier__c
fields.description: Calculated ratio used to compute Prorated Price.

fields.name: SBQQ__ProratedListPrice__c
fields.description: Prorated list unit price.

fields.name: SBQQ__ProratedPrice__c
fields.description: Prorated price for the product quoted by this line item. This price will only differ from Special Price if the product is a subscription and the line item is being prorated.

fields.name: SBQQ__Quantity__c
fields.description: Quantity being quoted.

fields.name: SBQQ__Quote__c
fields.description: Quote to which this line item belongs.

fields.name: SBQQ__RegularPrice__c
fields.description: Unit price before additional discount.

fields.name: SBQQ__RegularTotal__c
fields.description: Unit price before additional discount multiplied by quantity.

fields.name: SBQQ__Renewal__c
fields.description: Indicates this line item represents a product being renewed. Only non-subscription products for quote type "Renewal" will have this field set to true. Under normal circumstances this field should not be modified via UI.

fields.name: SBQQ__RenewedAsset__c
fields.description: Asset being renewed if this line item represents product renewal.

fields.name: SBQQ__RenewedSubscription__c
fields.description: Subscription being renewed by this quote line.

fields.name: SBQQ__RequiredBy__c
fields.description: Links this line to another line in the same quote whose product requires this line's product.

fields.name: SBQQ__SegmentIndex__c
fields.description: For multi-segmented Products, Index representing this Quote Line's position in the segment table.

fields.name: SBQQ__SegmentKey__c
fields.description: For multi-segmented Products, this is a shared key used to group multi-dimensional Quote Lines together.

fields.name: SBQQ__SegmentLabel__c
fields.description: For multi-segmented Products, this is the Column header label (e.g. "Year 1") associated with this line.

fields.name: SBQQ__Source__c
fields.description: Source of cloned quote line.

fields.name: SBQQ__SpecialPriceDescription__c
fields.description: Name of the Discount Tier or description of Contracted Price that generated special price for this line item

fields.name: SBQQ__SpecialPriceType__c
fields.description: Stores the type of special price offered on this line item. Null value indicates there is no special pricing. Under normal circumstances this field should not be modified via UI.

fields.name: SBQQ__SpecialPrice__c
fields.description: Special (volume-discounted or contracted) unit price for the product being quoted by this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__StartDate__c
fields.description: Date the service represented by this line item will begin (only applies if product is a subscription).

fields.name: SBQQ__SubscribedAssetIds__c
fields.description: Comma separated list of asset IDs covered by this subscription line. Only applicable to renewal quotes.

fields.name: SBQQ__SubscriptionBase__c
fields.description: Determines the price that serves as the base for percent-of-total calculations.

fields.name: SBQQ__SubscriptionCategory__c
fields.description: Category defined on the product to limit percent-of-total calculations to certain products. Copied from the product record.

fields.name: SBQQ__SubscriptionPercent__c
fields.description: Percent of non-subscription total to be used as the price of this subscription.

fields.name: SBQQ__SubscriptionPricing__c
fields.description: Method of calculating the subscription price. A blank value indicates that the line item isn't a subscription product.

fields.name: SBQQ__SubscriptionScope__c
fields.description: Determines how percent of total product prices are calculated. If scope is set to "Quote" any non-subscription and include in percent of total product is used in calculating every percent of total price. If scope is set to "Group" only products in the same group as the percent of total product are used in calculation.

fields.name: SBQQ__SubscriptionTargetPrice__c
fields.description: Price of the subscription target product on which maintenance should calculate.

fields.name: SBQQ__SubscriptionTerm__c
fields.description: Term for the subscription product in this line. If the product is not a subscription this value has no effect.

fields.name: SBQQ__SubscriptionType__c
fields.description: Indicates the subscription type to determine contract's pricing.

fields.name: SBQQ__TaxCode__c
fields.description: Specifies the tax code for taxation rules.

fields.name: SBQQ__Taxable__c
fields.description: Is this line item taxable.

fields.name: SBQQ__TermDiscountSchedule__c
fields.description: Schedule for discounts based on subscription term. This is useful when you want to show a breakdown of payments in separate groups, for different terms, yet you want to discount reflected for the entire duration of the subscription. Leave Term Discount Level blank if you want discount schedules applied based on the term of each line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__TermDiscountTier__c
fields.description: Tier within the term discount schedule used to discount this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__TermDiscount__c
fields.description: Discount calculated by applying subscription term against term discount schedule.

fields.name: SBQQ__TotalDiscountAmount__c
fields.description: Total discount amount for this line item including volume discount, contracted discount, and additional discount.

fields.name: SBQQ__TotalDiscountRate__c
fields.description: Total discount for this line item including volume discount, contracted discount, and additional discount.

fields.name: SBQQ__UnitCost__c
fields.description: Cost for one unit of product quoted on this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__UnproratedNetPrice__c
fields.description: The full-term Net Price.

fields.name: SBQQ__UpgradedAsset__c
fields.description: Asset being upgraded by this quote line. Only populated if this quote line represents an upgrade.

fields.name: SBQQ__UpgradedQuantity__c
fields.description: Quantity being upgraded.

fields.name: SBQQ__UpgradedSubscription__c
fields.description: Subscription being upgraded by this quote line.

fields.name: SBQQ__UpliftAmount__c
fields.description: Uplift (Amt) is measured as a currency amount. This is a system-calculated field, as Uplift can only be applied to MDQ segments in percent.

fields.name: SBQQ__Uplift__c

fields.name: SBQQ__DistributorDiscount__c

This is useful when you want to show a breakdown of payments in separate groups, for different terms, yet you want to discount reflected for the entire duration of the subscription. name: Web Quote Line
description: Line item on a Web Quote.

fields.name: External_ID__c
fields.description: Used by Data Packs to identify and update records.

fields.name: SBQQ__AdditionalDiscountAmount__c
fields.description: Additional customer discount extended on this line item in terms of absolute amount.

fields.name: SBQQ__AdditionalDiscount__c
fields.description: Total additional discount extends on this line item. Additional discount is defined as discount extended on top of volume discount or negotiated prices.

fields.name: SBQQ__AdditionalQuantity__c
fields.description: Additional quantity for this product that contributes to volume discount calculations.

fields.name: SBQQ__BatchQuantity__c
fields.description: For products sold in batches quantity in each batch. Defaulted from the product record.

fields.name: SBQQ__BlockPrice__c
fields.description: Block Price record used to price this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__Bundle__c
fields.description: Indicates this line item represents a package -- meaning it includes other line items in this quote.

fields.name: SBQQ__BundledQuantity__c
fields.description: For items with calculated quantities this field holds the original quantity entered by the user.

fields.name: SBQQ__Bundled__c
fields.description: Indicates the product on this line item is bundled (included) by another product in this quote. Bundled lines items have a zero price and do not allow price or quantity to be edited.

fields.name: SBQQ__ComponentCost__c
fields.description: Total cost of components in this package.

fields.name: SBQQ__ComponentDiscountedByPackage__c
fields.description: Fixes additional discount for this component to the parent package discount.

fields.name: SBQQ__ComponentListTotal__c
fields.description: Total list amount of components in this configuration. This field is only populated if this line item references a configurable product.

fields.name: SBQQ__ComponentSubscriptionScope__c
fields.description: Subscription scope set at the component level. This field overrides the subscription scope copied from the product.

fields.name: SBQQ__ComponentTotal__c
fields.description: Sum total amount of components in this configuration. This field is only populated if this line item references a configurable product.

fields.name: SBQQ__ComponentUpliftedByPackage__c
fields.description: Fixes uplift for this component to the parent package uplift. Uplift only applies to multi-segmented products.

fields.name: SBQQ__ComponentVisibility__c
fields.description: Indicates the visibility of the component line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__CompoundDiscountRate__c
fields.description: Discount rate compounded by quantity (historic).

fields.name: SBQQ__ConfigurationRequired__c
fields.description: Flag that marks this quote line as requiring configuration. Can be used by custom code to request this product be re-configured.

fields.name: SBQQ__ContractedPrice__c
fields.description: Contracted price if the product has negotiated pricing for the opportunity's account.

fields.name: SBQQ__CostEditable__c
fields.description: Specifies whether cost can be edited on this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__Cost__c
fields.description: Cost record used to cost this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__CustomerPrice__c
fields.description: Customer unit price for the product quoted by this line item. This is the Net Unit Price excluding any partner discounts.

fields.name: SBQQ__CustomerTotal__c
fields.description: Customer total price for this quote line item. This is the Net Total excluding any partner discounts.

fields.name: SBQQ__DefaultSubscriptionTerm__c
fields.description: Term length of the subscription, which only applies if the product is a subscription. It is copied from the Subscription Term of the related product when the line item is first generated.

fields.name: SBQQ__Description__c
fields.description: Description for this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__Dimension__c
fields.description: For MDQ products, this allows each segment to be priced independently.

fields.name: SBQQ__DiscountScheduleType__c
fields.description: Discount schedule type. Must be a stored value because it's used in formula fields that are rolled up.

fields.name: SBQQ__DiscountSchedule__c
fields.description: Discount schedule to be used in computing volume unit price. This field is copied from the corresponding product.

fields.name: SBQQ__DiscountTier__c
fields.description: Discount tier used by this line item. This field is only populated if a volume discounted was applied and discount schedule is of type "Range".

fields.name: SBQQ__Discount__c
fields.description: Additional customer discount extended for this line item expressed in terms of percentage.

fields.name: SBQQ__DistributorDiscount__c
fields.description: Distributor discount applied to this line.

fields.name: SBQQ__EffectiveEndDate__c
fields.description: Effective end date for this subscription.

fields.name: SBQQ__EffectiveQuantity__c
fields.description: Effective quantity used in computing totals. Same as quantity unless the product is block priced or covered by "Slab" discount schedule.

fields.name: SBQQ__EffectiveStartDate__c
fields.description: Effective start date for this subscription.

fields.name: SBQQ__EndDate__c
fields.description: Date the service represented by this line item will end (only applies if product is a subscription).

fields.name: SBQQ__Existing__c
fields.description: Indicates whether customer already owns this product. This is typically used for products with options during add-on quoting. The product is on the quote solely to drive the Configurator.

fields.name: SBQQ__GrossProfit__c
fields.description: Gross profit amount on this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__Hidden__c
fields.description: Hides this line item from generated PDF.

fields.name: SBQQ__Incomplete__c
fields.description: Flag set internally by the application logic when a line is saved to the database that's incomplete. This may happen when price rules are evaluated. Test this field in validation rules to avoid them from firing prematurely. Do NOT add to page layout or otherwise update.

fields.name: SBQQ__ListPrice__c
fields.description: List unit price for the product quoted by this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__ListTotal__c
fields.description: List total price for this quote line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__MarkupAmount__c
fields.description: Markup on this line item in the form of an absolute amount.

fields.name: SBQQ__MarkupRate__c
fields.description: Markup on this line item in the form of a percentage.

fields.name: SBQQ__Markup__c
fields.description: Markup amount on this item. This value is automatically calculated by applying markup rate or absolute amount, whichever is specified.

fields.name: SBQQ__MaximumPrice__c
fields.description: Maximum unit price for this product. Used to enforce price ceiling for products with dynamically calculated prices.

fields.name: SBQQ__MinimumPrice__c
fields.description: Minimum unit price for this product. Used to enforce price floor for products with dynamically calculated prices.

fields.name: SBQQ__NetPrice__c
fields.description: List unit price for the product quoted by this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__NetTotal__c
fields.description: Net total price for this quote line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__NonDiscountable__c
fields.description: Indicates whether this line item is non-discountable.

fields.name: SBQQ__NonPartnerDiscountable__c
fields.description: Indicates that this line item is non-discountable for partners.

fields.name: SBQQ__Number__c
fields.description: Number indicating this line's position within its group or quote.

fields.name: SBQQ__OptionDiscountAmount__c
fields.description: Discount extended on this product because it's part of a package.

fields.name: SBQQ__OptionDiscount__c
fields.description: If this line is for an optional SKU, this field captures any discount given to the package and extended to the option.

fields.name: SBQQ__OptionLevel__c
fields.description: Indicates nest level of this option (only applies to lines that are generated from options).

fields.name: SBQQ__OptionType__c
fields.description: Option type copied from related Product Option. Determines how quantity is calculated.

fields.name: SBQQ__Optional__c
fields.description: Marks this line as optional. Optional line items don't contribute to quote totals and are not transferred to the Opportunity.

fields.name: SBQQ__PackageCost__c
fields.description: Total cost for this package including the cost of its components.

fields.name: SBQQ__PackageListTotal__c
fields.description: Total list price of this package including its components.

fields.name: SBQQ__PackageProductCode__c
fields.description: Product code for the package generated by appending codes of selected components according to specified pattern.

fields.name: SBQQ__PackageTotal__c
fields.description: Total price of this package including its components.

fields.name: SBQQ__PartnerDiscount__c
fields.description: Partner discounts are applied after all automatic and discretionary discounts. The partner discount is taken into account in the Partner Price.

fields.name: SBQQ__PartnerPrice__c
fields.description: Partner unit price. Price after partner discount but before distributor discount.

fields.name: SBQQ__PartnerTotal__c
fields.description: Partner total

fields.name: SBQQ__PriceEditable__c
fields.description: Flag indicating if this line item's price is editable.

fields.name: SBQQ__PricingMethodEditable__c
fields.description: Specifies whether pricing method can be edited on this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__PricingMethod__c
fields.description: Determines how the price for this line item is set. List means it's calculated by subtracting discount from list price. Cost means it's calculated by adding markup to cost.

fields.name: SBQQ__PriorQuantity__c
fields.description: Combined quantity of this product from prior purchases.

fields.name: SBQQ__ProductCode__c
fields.description: Code for the product referenced by this line.

fields.name: SBQQ__ProductFamily__c
fields.description: Product Family for the product referenced by this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__ProductName__c
fields.description: Name for the product referenced by this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__ProductOption__c
fields.description: Product option that generated this line (if any).

fields.name: SBQQ__Product__c
fields.description: Product quoted by this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__ProrateMultiplier__c
fields.description: Calculated ratio used to compute Prorated Price.

fields.name: SBQQ__ProratedListPrice__c
fields.description: Prorated list unit price.

fields.name: SBQQ__ProratedPrice__c
fields.description: Prorated price for the product quoted by this line item. This price will only differ from Special Price if the product is a subscription and the line item is being prorated.

fields.name: SBQQ__Quantity__c
fields.description: Quantity of the line item being quoted.

fields.name: SBQQ__Quote__c
fields.description: Parent quote record.

fields.name: SBQQ__RegularPrice__c
fields.description: Unit price before additional discounts are applied.

fields.name: SBQQ__Renewal__c
fields.description: Indicates this line item represents a product being renewed. Only non-subscription products for quote type "Renewal" will have this field set to true. Under normal circumstances this field should not be modified via UI.

fields.name: SBQQ__RenewedAsset__c
fields.description: Asset being renewed if this line item represents a product renewal.

fields.name: SBQQ__RenewedSubscription__c
fields.description: Subscription being renewed by this quote line.

fields.name: SBQQ__RequiredBy__c
fields.description: Links this line to another line in the same quote whose product requires this line's product.

fields.name: SBQQ__SegmentIndex__c
fields.description: For multi-segmented Products, Index representing this Quote Line's position in the segment table.

fields.name: SBQQ__SegmentKey__c
fields.description: This represents the segment that contains a unique value.

fields.name: SBQQ__SegmentLabel__c
fields.description: This is the Column header label associated with this line.

fields.name: SBQQ__Source__c
fields.description: Source of cloned quote line.

fields.name: SBQQ__SpecialPriceDescription__c
fields.description: Name of the Discount Tier or description of Contracted Price that generated special price for this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__SpecialPriceType__c
fields.description: Stores the type of special price offered on this line item. Null value indicates there is no special pricing. Under normal circumstances this field should not be modified via UI.

fields.name: SBQQ__SpecialPrice__c
fields.description: Special (volume-discounted or contracted) unit price for the product being quoted by this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__StartDate__c
fields.description: Date the service represented by this line item will begin (only applies if product is a subscription).

fields.name: SBQQ__SubscribedAssetIds__c
fields.description: Comma separated list of asset IDs covered by this subscription line. Only applicable to renewal quotes.

fields.name: SBQQ__SubscriptionBase__c
fields.description: Determines whether dynamic subscriptions are calculated off List, Customer or Net product price.

fields.name: SBQQ__SubscriptionCategory__c
fields.description: Category defined on the product to limit percent-of-total calculations to certain products.

fields.name: SBQQ__SubscriptionPercent__c
fields.description: Percent of non-subscription product total to be used as the price of this subscription.

fields.name: SBQQ__SubscriptionPricing__c
fields.description: Method of calculating the subscription price. A blank value indicates that the line item isn't a subscription product.

fields.name: SBQQ__SubscriptionScope__c
fields.description: Determines how dynamic subscription prices are calculated. If scope is set to "Quote" any non-subscription product is used in calculating every dynamic subscription. If scope is set to "Group" only products in the same group as the dynamic subscription are used.

fields.name: SBQQ__SubscriptionTargetPrice__c
fields.description: Price of the subscription target product on which maintenance should calculate.

fields.name: SBQQ__SubscriptionTerm__c
fields.description: Term for the subscription product in this line. If the product is not a subscription this value has no effect.

fields.name: SBQQ__Taxable__c
fields.description: Indicates if the line item is taxable.

fields.name: SBQQ__TermDiscountSchedule__c
fields.description: Schedule for discounts based on subscription term.

fields.name: SBQQ__TermDiscountTier__c
fields.description: Tier within the term discount schedule used to discount this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__TermDiscount__c
fields.description: Discount calculated by applying subscription term against term discount schedule.

fields.name: SBQQ__TotalDiscountAmount__c
fields.description: Total discount for this line item including volume discount, contracted discount, and additional discount.

fields.name: SBQQ__UnitCost__c
fields.description: Cost for one unit of product quoted on this line item.

fields.name: SBQQ__UpgradedAsset__c
fields.description: Asset being upgraded by this quote line. Only populated if this quote line represents an upgrade.

fields.name: SBQQ__UpgradedSubscription__c
fields.description: Subscription being upgraded by this quote line.

fields.name: SBQQ__UpliftAmount__c
fields.description: This is measured as a currency amount. This is a system-calculated field and Uplift can only be applied in %.

fields.name: SBQQ__Uplift__c
fields.description: This is measured as a percent.

fields.name: SBQQ__VolumeDiscount__c
fields.description: Volume discount in amount of Opportunity's currency applied to this line item.

name: Web Quote
description: Quote originated by external parties such as customers or partners from a Portal or Force.com Site. This object offers a subset of functionality of the full Quote object but does not require an Opportunity.

fields.name: External_ID__c
fields.description: Used by Data Packs to identify and update records.

fields.name: SBQQ__Account__c
fields.description: Customer account. Defaulted on create from the opportunity.

fields.name: SBQQ__AdditionalDiscountAmount__c
fields.description: Amount of additional discount on this quote.

fields.name: SBQQ__AverageCustomerDiscount__c
fields.description: Average customer discount (in percent) for this quote.

fields.name: SBQQ__AveragePartnerDiscount__c
fields.description: Average partner discount (in percent) for this quote.

fields.name: SBQQ__BatchQuantity__c
fields.description: For products sold in batches quantity in each batch. Defaulted from the product record.

fields.name: SBQQ__BillingCity__c
fields.description: City of the Bill To address for this quote.

fields.name: SBQQ__BillingCountry__c
fields.description: Country of the Bill To address for this quote.

fields.name: SBQQ__BillingName__c
fields.description: Name for the Bill To address.

fields.name: SBQQ__BillingPostalCode__c
fields.description: Postal Code of the Bill To address for this quote.

fields.name: SBQQ__BillingState__c
fields.description: State/Province of the Bill To address for this quote.

fields.name: SBQQ__BillingStreet__c
fields.description: Street portion of the billing address for this quote.

fields.name: SBQQ__CustomerAmount__c
fields.description: Roll up summary of the Customer Amount.

fields.name: SBQQ__CustomerDiscount__c
fields.description: Additional discount extended to customer.

fields.name: SBQQ__DaysQuoteOpen__c
fields.description: Number of days the quote has been open.

fields.name: SBQQ__DefaultTemplate__c
fields.description: Template that should be used with this quote. Salesforce CPQ will use this value to default template selection on "Generate Document" screen.

fields.name: SBQQ__DeliveryMethod__c
fields.description: Method used to deliver products in this quote.

fields.name: SBQQ__DistributorDiscount__c
fields.description: Distributor discount that applies to this quote unless overridden on line item level.

fields.name: SBQQ__DocumentId__c
fields.description: ID of the Document record which contains the generated document.

fields.name: SBQQ__EmailTemplateId__c
fields.description: ID of email template that will be pre-populated when documents generated from this quote are emailed.

fields.name: SBQQ__EndDate__c
fields.description: End date for subscriptions in this group.

fields.name: SBQQ__ExpirationDate__c
fields.description: Date after which the Quote is no longer valid.

fields.name: SBQQ__FirstSegmentTermEndDate__c
fields.description: Used with multi-segment Products to prorate first segment.

fields.name: SBQQ__Introduction__c
fields.description: Introduction that can be printed on the generated PDF document.

fields.name: SBQQ__LineItemCount__c
fields.description: Number of line items in this quote.

fields.name: SBQQ__ListAmount__c
fields.description: Total List Amount of each non-optional line item in this quote.

fields.name: SBQQ__MarkupRate__c
fields.description: Default markup rate applied to line items on this quote.

fields.name: SBQQ__MasterContract__c
fields.description: Master contract with which subscription products in this quote are to be co-terminated.

fields.name: SBQQ__NetAmount__c
fields.description: Total Net Amount of each non-optional line item in this quote.

fields.name: SBQQ__Notes__c
fields.description: Notes printed on the generated PDF document.

fields.name: SBQQ__Opportunity__c
fields.description: Opportunity being quoted.

fields.name: SBQQ__OriginalQuote__c
fields.description: If the quote is an Amend Re-Quote this field points to the original quote.

fields.name: SBQQ__PartnerDiscount__c
fields.description: Discount extended to partner on this opportunity.

fields.name: SBQQ__PaymentTerms__c
fields.description: Terms that govern payment of the items in this quote.

fields.name: SBQQ__PriceBook__c

Why do this project?

fields.name: tspa__EnableMonitoring__c
fields.description: The setting enables or disables the Platform Events Monitoring. Disabling this setting will stop the monitoring process, and disable all types of alerts (emails, logs, and warnings to the agent) if the platform events quota passes the thresholds.

fields.name: tspa__NotificationIntervalsInHours__c
fields.description: The settings set the maximum frequency that the email notification will be sent, set in hours. the recommended value is 12 hours. Minimum value is 1 hour.

fields.name: tspa__SupportEmail__c
fields.description: The setting has the email address Visual Remote Assistant support which will get the email with a notification about the platform events quota threshold reached. It can have one email address.

fields.name: tspa__SystemAdminEmail__c
fields.description: The setting has a list of emails that will get the email with a notification about the platform events quota thresholds passed. It can have up to three email addresses, the emails must be separated by commas without spaces.

fields.name: tspa__Threshold1__c
fields.description:
Threshold 1 set the threshold in percentage from the org quota (either published platform events or delivered platform events) that will trigger log notifications and email alerts (based on email settings). 
threshold 1 should be less than threshold 2.

fields.name: tspa__Threshold2__c
fields.description:
Threshold 2 set the threshold in percentage from the org quota (either published platform events or delivered platform events) that will trigger an agent warning on top of the logs and email alerts.
Threshold 2 should be higher than threshold 1.
